    "description": "Alteplase is a recombinant tissue plasminogen activator (tPA) used primarily as a thrombolytic agent to dissolve blood clots in conditions such as acute ischemic stroke, myocardial infarction (heart attack), and pulmonary embolism. By converting plasminogen to plasmin, Alteplase helps to break down fibrin, leading to the restoration of blood flow in blocked arteries, thus alleviating symptoms and preventing further tissue damage.",
    "uses": "Alteplase is primarily indicated for the treatment of acute ischemic stroke when administered within a specific time frame of the onset of symptoms. It is also used in cases of myocardial infarction to rapidly dissolve coronary artery thrombi, improving survival rates and outcomes. Additionally, Alteplase is utilized in treating pulmonary embolism to relieve obstruction of pulmonary arteries, particularly in patients who are hemodynamically unstable.\nMoreover, Alteplase may be used off-label in certain conditions such as catheter occlusion and occasionally in severe cases of deep vein thrombosis where rapid thrombolysis is warranted.",
    "side effects": [
      "Bleeding: Alteplase can increase the risk of bleeding, including serious internal bleeding and hemorrhagic stroke.",
      "Allergic reactions: Some patients may experience allergic reactions, ranging from mild rash to more severe anaphylactic reactions.",
      "Nausea and vomiting: Gastrointestinal side effects such as nausea or vomiting may occur in some patients.",
      "Hypotension: There may be a drop in blood pressure, especially in the setting of significant bleeding.",
      "Arrhythmias: Alteplase may potentially cause abnormal heart rhythms, particularly during its infusion."
    ]
